## Log format standard

All Phase 5 tests MUST use structured logging for debuggability:

```
[PHASE_ID][test=TEST_NAME][step=STEP] message | key1=value1 key2=value2
```

Example:
```
[5A3][test=create_table_alloc][step=allocate] page_num=2 page_type=leaf
[5A3][test=create_table_alloc][step=sqlite_master] type=table name=t rootpage=2
[5A3][test=create_table_alloc][step=verify] sqlite_master_entries=1 ✓
```

## Diagnostic dump on failure

Every test that modifies the database should implement:
```rust
fn dump_state(conn: &Connection) {
    eprintln!("[DIAG] page_count={}", conn.page_count());
    eprintln!("[DIAG] schema_version={}", conn.schema_version());
    eprintln!("[DIAG] wal_frames={}", conn.wal_frame_count());
    for entry in conn.query("SELECT * FROM sqlite_master") {
        eprintln!("[DIAG] sqlite_master: {entry:?}");
    }
}
```

Call this in test failure handlers or via `#[should_panic]` test wrappers.

## Timing

Wrap significant operations in timing:
```rust
let start = Instant::now();
conn.execute("INSERT INTO t VALUES (1)").unwrap();
eprintln!("[5B2][test=insert][step=execute] elapsed_us={}", start.elapsed().as_micros());
```

